ough the dynamic-access report reached `3/3 (100.00%)`. The preserved branch also does not contain `metadata/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation/opentelemetry-jdbc/2.28.1-alpha/reachability-metadata.json`, so the run never finalized a valid new-library output.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `logs/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation:opentelemetry-jdbc:2.28.1-alpha/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-26T18-40-01-423734Z.log`\n- `logs/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation:opentelemetry-jdbc:2.28.1-alpha/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-26T18-40-01-454129Z.log`\n- `logs/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation:opentelemetry-jdbc:2.28.1-alpha/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-06-26T18-41-46-411355Z.log`\n- `logs/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation:opentelemetry-jdbc:2.28.1-alpha/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-26T19-01-00-041004Z.log`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Check out the preserved branch and review whether the proxy-based `JdbcUtilsTest` plus test-local metadata are acceptable for this new-library request.\n2. Add and validate the missing library metadata file `metadata/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation/opentelemetry-jdbc/2.28.1-alpha/reachability-metadata.json` if support should be kept.\n3. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.opentelemetry.instrumentation:opentelemetry-jdbc:2.28.1-alpha` and regenerate the final artifacts/metrics from the preserved branch."}}
